SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ADMINISTRATIVE MANAGER REVIEWS THE FORM 990 AND THEN PROVIDES IT TO THE TRUSTEES TO REVIEW PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE TRUSTEES ARE REQUIRED TO COMPLY WITH THE REQUIREMENTS OF THE EMPLOYEE RETIREMENT INCOME SECURITY ACT OF 1974 (ERISA), AS WELL AS THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (IRC), AND THE ATTENDANT REGULATIONS ADOPTED PURSUANT TO BOTH ERISA AND IRC, WITH RESPECT TO NON-EXEMPT PROHIBITED TRANSACTIONS. A MEMBER OF THE PLAN'S LEGAL COUNSEL ATTENDS EACH MEETING OF THE TRUSTEES AND MONITORS ON AN "AS NEEDED" BASIS FOR ANY ACTIVITY THAT COULD GIVE RISE TO POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE TRUSTEES EVALUATE AND ADJUST THE COMPENSATION OF THE ADMINISTRATIVE MANAGER AND OTHER MANAGERIAL PERSONNEL UTILIZING LOCAL MARKET KNOWLEDGE AND EVALUATION OF JOB PERFORMANCE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PLAN PROVIDES THE FORM 990 UPON WRITTEN REQUEST FROM THE PUBLIC. THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS ARE NOT PROVIDED TO THE PUBLIC.

COLLECTION FEES 22,769. MEMBERSHIP FEES 21,345. FEDERAL EXCISE TAX 17,366. PENSION BENEFIT GUARANTEED 11,931. COMPUTER LICENSING FEES 8,944. MISCELLANEOUS 2,609. ALLOCATED TO ANNUITY TRUST -333,473. ALLOCATED TO PENSION TRUST -597,466.
THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES IS CHARGED WITH OVERSIGHT OF THE INDEPENDENT AUDIT. THIS PROCESS IS CONSISTENT WITH THE PRIOR YEAR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART I, LINE 5 AND PART V, LINE 2A:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE NUMBER OF EMPLOYEES EXCLUDES PARTICIPANT DISABILITY PAYMENTS, WHICH ARE CLASSIFIED AS BENEFITS EXPENSE. A TOTAL OF 168 W-2S WERE ISSUED TO PARTICIPANTS RECEIVING DISABILITY PAYMENTS IN 2022.
THE PLAN DIRECTLY ISSUES 1099S TO MEDICAL PROVIDERS FOR DENTAL AND VISION SERVICES.
